Imper.) mulier ad me transeat. Eadem is normally found with Asyndeton, though in Poen. 617 (quoted in note on v. 457), if the reading bc right, we have atque eadem. (In Stich. 451 eadem P, atque eadem A.) Eadem opera has a Conjunction in Bacch. 60 Tu prohibebis et cadem opera tuo sodali operam dabis, Most. 1039 Sume: eademque opera <cyo> baec tihi uarrauero.
